  "text": "In this paper, we show how a clique tree of a chordal graph H can be computed from a pmo of H by building the maximal cliques one after the other, and how general algorithm MLS can be modified in order to compute a pmo, a clique tree and the minimal separators of any chordal graph for any labeling structure. We also give a necessary and sufficient condition on a labeling structure (which is not satisfied by L LexDF S ) for new cliques to be detected by a condition on labels. As MLS can be used to compute a peo of the complement graph of the input graph if it is chordal [CITATION_1] , we further modify it to compute a pmo and a clique tree of the complement graph, and we show that new cliques in the complement graph can be detected by a condition on labels for any labeling structure. We also provide a linear time algorithm computing a pmo and the generators of the maximal cliques and minimal separators w.r.t. this pmo of the complement graph.",
